data.description: As its moniker suggests, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Shadow 2.0’ utilizes the same neutral palette featured on the original Black/Grey colorway from 1985. This pair makes use of a black leather upper with grey suede overlays at the toe and heel. A matching grey Swoosh is joined by traditional branding elements that include a Nike Air tongue tag and a Jordan Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar. A rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air cushioning delivers a smooth ride.
data.name: Jordan 1 Retro High Shadow 2.0

data.description: The Power Rangers x Reebok Club C ‘Saber-Toothed Tiger Zord’ is taken from a nostalgic capsule collection celebrating the ‘90s television series. This pair draws inspiration from the Yellow Ranger’s battle craft, featuring a yellow leather upper marked with colorful graphics lifted directly from the Zord. Its fangs are represented by the sneaker’s metallic silver heel tab. Mismatched tongue tags feature a Saber-Toothed Tiger graphic and the Power Rangers’ lightning bolt logo.
data.name: Reebok Club C Power Rangers Yellow

data.description: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Lightning’ resurrects a highly coveted colorway that originally launched in 2006 alongside an accompanying ‘Thunder’ colorway, both of which were inspired by Michael Jordan’s Motorsports team. A bright yellow hue floods the nubuck upper, contrasted by black netting and dark grey structural wings. Matching grey accents land on the woven tongue tag, interior tongue and Jumpman branding at the heel. A white PU midsole, enhanced with visible Air sole cushioning, rides on a dark grey herringbone rubber outsole.
data.name: Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021)

data.description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Electric Green’ showcases a simplistic two-tone color scheme that calls to mind an Oregon PE colorway that surfaced online in 2018. The iconic silhouette sports a black nubuck upper with contrasting hits of neon green on the tongue and spoiler-like pull tab. Tonal Jumpman branding is embroidered on the sneaker’s back heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a polyurethane midsole, enlivened with additional green pops and fitted with a visible Air sole unit. Underfoot, the semi-translucent rubber outsole is treated to a glow-in-the-dark finish.
data.name: Jordan 6 Retro Electric Green

data.description: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.
data.name: Yeezy 500 'Taupe Light'

data.description: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole.
data.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Mono Cinder'

data.description: The women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Blue Bird’ treats the retro silhouette to a vibrant makeover. An energetic shade of blue is executed on a suede upper furnished with standard AJ5 details, including lace locks, molded TPU eyelets and clear netting across the quarter panel. A blue Jumpman is embroidered atop a silver reflective tongue, complementing silver shark tooth detailing on the polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, an icy blue rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for maximum grip.
data.name: Wmns Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Blue Bird'

data.description: The Nike Zoom Kobe 6 Protro ‘White Del Sol’ brings back the original ‘POP’ colorway from 2011, updated with refreshed tooling and a sleeker shape. Polyurethane ‘islands’ create a scaly texture on the white and grey upper, fortified with a black molded heel counter and accented with a matching black Swoosh. The Cushlon midsole packs a large and flexible Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot, along with a softer foam compound in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a snakeskin-inspired traction pattern for maximum grip.
data.name: Kobe 6 Protro Playoff Pack White Del Sol

data.description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Michigan State’ delivers a low-top version of the Michigan State Dunk from 2020. Like its predecessor, the shoe features a two-tone all-leather upper rendered in classic ‘Be True to Your School’ color blocking. A stark white finish is contrasted by a dark green Swoosh and matching overlays at the toe and heel. Standard Nike branding hits decorate the heel and nylon tongue. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber outsole, complete with a traction pattern originally developed for the hardwood.
data.name: Nike Dunk Low Spartan Green
Air Zoom Infinity Tour NRG 'Hydrogen Blue Crimson Tint'

data.description: The Reebok Question Low ‘White Grey’ delivers a neutral take on Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe, highlighted by a white tumbled leather upper with subtle grey accents. The refined color scheme recalls a similar 1999 release, which featured a grey suede toe cap instead of this pair’s patent leather overlay. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an EVA midsole with Hexalite pods in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole offers reliable traction.
data.name: Reebok Question Low Grey Toe
Nike Dunk Low Olive Brown Orange

data.description: The Saucony Mad River 2 TR ‘Water’ is taken from the ‘Astrotrail Pack,’ featuring a quartet of trail running shoes inspired by astrology and the four elements of the natural world. This pair showcases a gradient two-tone finish on a breathable textile upper, reinforced with synthetic overlays and secured with a drawcord lacing system. Common to all four models in the collection are a speckled midsole and a birthstone zodiac symbol on the webbing pull tab affixed to the tongue.
data.name: Mad River 2 TR 'Astrotrail Pack - Water'
Nike Kyrie 4 EP Black Turf Orange

data.description: The adidas Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange' carries a breathable jacquard mesh upper with wavy overlays in contrasting black and burnt orange accents. The mid-top is equipped with a stretchy neoprene collar and fortified with a synthetic suede toe cap. A seamless heel counter extends to the midsole, packed with full-length Boost cushioning wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a classic herringbone tread for stop-and-go traction.
data.name: Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange'

data.description: The Nike Air Force 1 '07 LV8 ‘Fresh’ treats the classic silhouette to a design refresh with eye-catching accents. The upper is constructed from white leather with a metallic iridescent trim outlining the sneaker’s various overlays. Glossy black patent leather is utilized on the Swoosh and heel tab, marked with a standard Nike Air logo in gradient yellow and red coloring. A similar color-fade effect is applied to the lace aglets and raised Air branding on the midsole.
data.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Fresh
